              <span id="reviewTextContainer1388728214" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3722581364948340786">I wasn&apos;t sure I would enjoy this book when I started it. It seemed a little disjointed and difficult to follow. However, now that I have finished, I thing the incongruities are an intentional part of the atmosphere. Nancy Collins has put forth some interesting ideas regarding the nature of vampires in this book that fans of the genre will no doubt find interesting. I&apos;m not sure if I will continue reading the series, but I did end up liking this one.</span>
  <span id="freeText3722581364948340786" style="display:none">I wasn't sure I would enjoy this book when I started it. It seemed a little disjointed and difficult to follow. However, now that I have finished, I thing the incongruities are an intentional part of the atmosphere. Nancy Collins has put forth some interesting ideas regarding the nature of vampires in this book that fans of the genre will no doubt find interesting. I'm not sure if I will continue reading the series, but I did end up liking this one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3722581364948340786" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


