<span id="freeTextContainer4614363770573855295">Not sure how I&apos;d forgotten the truly nightmarish nature of this book. I&apos;ve read quite a lot by Nancy A Collins, but none as dark and hideous as this. There are no redeeming characters, everything is exploitative, violent, revolting and shocking. It kind of loses the impact after a while, which is rather alarming in retrospect.<br/><br/>I can&apos;t really recommend it, but admire it&apos;s unflinching habitation of horror and recognise some of the internal visions of the characters.</span>
