  <span id="freeText5858233253981077168" style="display:none">Sonya Blue is one tough vampire and I liked the dark and edgy feeling to it. This is no vampire romance, but a cool look at vampires as a subculture in our times.<br /><br />Adding a review I wrote in 1992, which I just found in an old book-diary.<br /><br />Sonja Blue is a vampire, but inside her is still the girl Denise Thorne. The good and the evil are fighting for dominance. Helping her is Claude Hagerty, who was a guard in the asylum she was kept in.<br /><br />She is a likable character and a very well written book. I enjoyed it very much and I will be looking forward to other books by Nancy Collins, because she has a new approach to vampires. </span>
